** Who are we? **

Chamonix IT Solutions is an end-to-end technical services business focused on
helping customers to achieve and maintain digital currency to stay competitive
in an ever-evolving market. From digital transformation through to complete
technical delivery and ongoing managed support, Chamonix has been working with
customers across a range of industries for over 12 years to understand where
they are on their digital journey, where they need to be and then help them
get there.

Based at Brisbane’s innovation hub, The Precinct, with operations growing in
Queensland, we’re at the forefront of technology and our people are the
driving force behind our success. We foster a strong culture of collaboration,
continuous learning and constantly seek new ways to deliver the very best
outcomes for our customers.

** How will you help contribute to our success? **

  * Participate in delivery of multiple integration solution types in a range of customer environments 
  * Deliver end-to-end development of an integration solution and controlling the conformance of its implementation 
  * Design and create modern integration solutions to solve client business problems in Azure 
  * Deploy automation for Azure via PowerShell and Azure Resource Manager 
  * Interpret the future state architecture and focus on best practice modern integration in cloud and hybrid environments 

** What skills does our ideal candidate have? **

  * Significant experience in delivering the end-to-end development of an integration solution in Azure. 
  * Experience with Azure Service Bus, Azure Logic Apps, or Azure API Management. 
  * Experience in MuleSoft with a strong understanding of Java and related technologies. 
  * Experience implementing automated build and deployment processes using PowerShell, Cake Build, Microsoft Azure DevOps or Atlassian Bamboo, Jenkins or Octopus Deploy. 
  * Boomi experience is highly desirable. 
  * Experience working in an agile environment, elaborating user stories & running iterations to rapidly design/build/deploy solutions. 
  * Well-developed interpersonal skills with demonstrated prior experience working in a client facing role. 

** What’s in it for you? **

  * Work with some of the brightest and best minds in Australia 
  * Come to work at The Precinct, Brisbane's hub of innovation 
  * Have the opportunity to be a mentor to future talent and develop our leaders of tomorrow 
  * Financial support and additional time off to complete professional development activities 

